                <h2 style="margin-bottom: 20px;">What is Multicultural Day?</h2>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Multicultural Day is an annual event celebrated at St Ives High School that brings together students, staff, and the wider community to celebrate the cultures of the world</p>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">There are cultural performances, food, music, and activities throughout the day as part of celebrations</p>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Multicultural Day has grown to become one of the most anticipated events at our school, fostering cross-cultural friendships, promoting cultural exchange, and encouraging open dialogues about identity and heritage.</p>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Our goal is to cultivate a sense of cultural appreciation and understanding among our students.</p>
                <p style="margin-bottom: 20px;">Multicultural Day plays a crucial role in giving students the chance to engage with cultures they may not be familiar with, challenging preconceived notions and broadening their perspectives.</p>
